We want you to be a part of building Sound’s Telemedicine service line as we launch the first nationally-scaled, fully-resourced, hospital medicine-focused telemedicine program. At Sound, we are eager to launch telemedicine as a new care delivery model and are excited to ramp up and provide the best telemedicine service across the nation. We hope you will join us!
Success Happens When you Start With your People

This innovative model of care delivery will help providers find balance and joy in their careers as they add a new dimension to their scope of practice.

Job Title: Collaborative Physician needed for a small low volume psych practice
Job Description:
Collaborative Psychiatrist for small Integrated (Family & Psych) practice.
We seek a Psychiatrist (MD, DO) to collaborate with a low-volume Nurse practitioner (two providers) owned and operated clinic.
Duties:
The Psychiatrist collaborates with the APRN(s) in the provision of psychiatric services to evaluate and diagnose adult patients utilizing DSM-5 criteria and develop a plan of care according to APA and SAMSHA best practice guidelines, including prescribing psychotropic medications.
The physician collaborator is available to the APRN(s) to meet the state supervisory regulations and intermittently available for clinical consultations.

Dr. Cannabus (www.DrCannabus.com) provides qualified patients with medical marijuana licensing via a mobile environment. Our goal is to make available via a custom mobile medical office, a caring, compassionate, patient experience for Florida residents to pursue a better quality of life through the many benefits of medical marijuana. In the past year, we’ve already established a strong area presence on the west coast of Florida from (Ft Meyers to Tampa) soon to expand across the state.
Instagram: @drcannabusofficial
DESCRIPTION:
We are looking for responsible and compassionate MDs that believe in medicinal cannabis as an alternative to traditional medication. You will be responsible for reviewing the patient's medical ailments, certifying, and & meeting the patient, and be comfortable and willing to sign off on medical cannabis certifications for a variety of conditions such as Anxiety, PTSD, Cancer, Severe Chronic Pain, IBD, Crohn's, Autism, etc.

As an alternative to opiates, medical marijuana is a fast-growing part of healthcare. We offer an affordable, efficient way for patients to obtain their medical marijuana certification.
After the patient books an appointment on our website, they will be added to your calendar based on your availability. We expect the average appointment to last 5-10 minutes, with some minor electronic paperwork subsequently.
In Florida, first-time patients are required to be seen in person. Renewals can be completed via Telehealth. We are looking for candidates who have the option to see patients in person. This would be ideal for Physicians who have a private practice and can see these patients throughout their regular workday or after hours - in their office.
The pay will be per-patient at a rate of $50 per-patient.

Thrivelab's Chief Medical Officer is Dr. Rothenberg, who has been a leading expert in hormone optimization, from writing multiple textbooks to teaching more than 50,000 physicians. The collaborating physician would receive training, support and collaboration from Dr. Rothenberg and our Assistant Medical Director Kris Hart.

Job Description:
We are looking to add another MD or DO to our growing private practice clinic!
Come work with a number of health care disciplines to provide top quality care to patients of all age ranges in the beautiful Brainerd Lakes area!
We are looking to hire amazing, passionate physicians that believe in providing the best care possible to patients while providing everyone with the proper autonomy with their own healthcare decisions.
No shot mandates required for employment!
Work in a well-established clinic that is well respected in the community. We are rapidly expanding and looking for a number of medical specialties, so if you are passionate about patient care and autonomy please apply!

North Sound Emergency Medicine, a well-established, large democratic provider group in Everett, Washington, is looking for an EM residency-trained BC/BP physician. This is a tremendous opportunity to join an exceptional team of clinicians who are dedicated to excellence, providing evidence-based patient care in a supportive environment, while offering opportunities for professional growth, education, and development.
Our practice site has a very stable contract and sees more than 90,000 patients annually in a state-of-the-art 79-bed ED; the largest and busiest ED in the state of Washington and the 10th busiest in the nation.
One of the most desirable places to live, the greater Seattle area offers an abundance of recreational activities from scuba diving and skiing to backpacking the Pacific Crest Trail, professional sports teams and a myriad of cultural amenities, ranging from opera and ballet to museums and theater.

Remote Telemedicine Opportunity — Competitive Pay ($120-$150/hr)
We are looking for a culturally responsive, well-respected clinical care professional available for weekdays, nights, weekends, or on-call shifts with a desire for supplemental income and an interest in telemedicine opportunities. Physicians will work closely with our platform partners (e.g., large employers, digital health start-ups) to conduct virtual visits via video, phone, connected devices, or asynchronous messages with patients. There are a variety of opportunities, including online urgent care, online concierge medicine, prescription review and approval, lab interpretation, mental health management, and more.
Physicians work independently and are responsible for diagnostic and therapeutic decision-making within industry and locally established standards of care, clinical practice guidelines, and organization policies and procedures. The content of medical decision-making focuses on common conditions that would present within an episodic, acute, or primary care medical practice.

We are the largest post-acute care group in the mideast, and we currently provide medical services to skilled nursing facilities in multiple states.
We are looking for new talent and are hiring Physicians to serve as medical director and attending physicians at skilled nursing facilities. This position will work closely with a team to provide care to nursing facility residents and continuously improve processes and quality of care.

Our practice site has a very stable contract and sees more than 90,000 patients annually in a state-of-the-art 79-bed ED; the largest and busiest ED in the state of Washington and the 10th busiest in the nation.
One of the most desirable places to live, the greater Seattle area offers an abundance of recreational activities from scuba diving and skiing to backpacking the Pacific Crest Trail, professional sports teams and a myriad of cultural amenities, ranging from opera and ballet to museums and theater.

Remote Telemedicine Opportunity — Competitive Pay ($120-$150/hr)

Our Company
Cerebral is a one-stop shop for high-quality mental health care.
Since launching in January 2020, we have gone from 5 people in an off brand WeWork to over 2,000 team members across the United States working hand in hand to transform access to high-quality mental health care at scale. Our team will not stop building, growing, and iterating until everyone, everywhere can access high-quality mental health care without the high cost, wait times, and stigma.
We recently became the fastest mental health company ever to unicorn status, having raised over $162 million and achieved a valuation above $1.2 billion raised. Cerebral's investors include Silver Lake, Access Industries, Bill Ackman, Chris Burch, WestCap, and Oak HC/FT.
It is just the beginning for Cerebral, and we need your help as we transform access to high-quality mental health care in the United States and beyond.

Remote Telemedicine Opportunity — Competitive Pay ($120-$150/hr)

Job Title: Collaborative Physician needed for a small low volume psych practice
Job Description:
Collaborative Psychiatrist for small Integrated (Family & Psych) practice.
We seek a Psychiatrist (MD, DO) to collaborate with a low-volume Nurse practitioner (two providers) owned and operated clinic.
Duties:
The Psychiatrist collaborates with the APRN(s) in the provision of psychiatric services to evaluate and diagnose adult patients utilizing DSM-5 criteria and develop a plan of care according to APA and SAMSHA best practice guidelines, including prescribing psychotropic medications.
The physician collaborator is available to the APRN(s) to meet the state supervisory regulations and intermittently available for clinical consultations.

Job Title: Physicians Wanted - P/T or F/T - Florida Licensed
Job Description:
Integrity Medical is a Progressive, Pro-Choice, Family-Planning medical practice and clinic.
We are seeking physicians of any specialty to provide medical care to women seeking family-planning services. Must possess a valid, current, license to practice medicine in the State of Florida. We will provide training. Any specialty welcome. FMGs welcome. GPs welcome.
Must be respectful and supportive of women, and of women's right to freedom of choice. Must be willing to help women seeking pro-choice family planning services and to provide medical care to these women in a kind, caring, and compassionate manner. Must be strongly supportive of women's rights.
Depending on how much you are willing to work and what services you are willing to provide, we offer compensation ranging from $100,000 per year for about 10 hours of work per week up, to $400,000 per year, or more.

Supervising Physician for Hormone Optimization Clinic (North Carolina)
Thrivelab is searching for a collaborating physician in North Carolina to oversee Nurse Practitioner for a regenerative medicine clinic that specializes in Bioidentical Hormone Optimization.
Thrivelab has Nurse Practitioners that see patients via home visits and telehealth consults. Physician would be responsible to satisfy regulatory requirements and support the Nurse Practitioners.
Thrivelab's Chief Medical Officer is Dr. Rothenberg, who has been a leading expert in hormone optimization, from writing multiple textbooks to teaching more than 50,000 physicians. The collaborating physician would receive training, support and collaboration from Dr. Rothenberg and our Assistant Medical Director Kris Hart.

This would be ideal for Physicians who have a private practice and can see these patients throughout their regular workday or after hours - in their office.
The pay will be per-patient at a rate of $50 per-patient.

Job Title: Physician - Primary Care - Brainerd/Baxter - NO SHOT MANDATES REQUIRED
Job Description:
We are looking to add another MD or DO to our growing private practice clinic!
Come work with a number of health care disciplines to provide top quality care to patients of all age ranges in the beautiful Brainerd Lakes area!
We are looking to hire amazing, passionate physicians that believe in providing the best care possible to patients while providing everyone with the proper autonomy with their own healthcare decisions.
No shot mandates required for employment!
Work in a well-established clinic that is well respected in the community. We are rapidly expanding and looking for a number of medical specialties, so if you are passionate about patient care and autonomy please apply!

Remote Telemedicine Opportunity — Competitive Pay ($120-$150/hr)
We are looking for a culturally responsive, well-respected clinical care professional available for weekdays, nights, weekends, or on-call shifts with a desire for supplemental income and an interest in telemedicine opportunities. Physicians will work closely with our platform partners (e.g., large employers, digital health start-ups) to conduct virtual visits via video, phone, connected devices, or asynchronous messages with patients. There are a variety of opportunities, including online urgent care, online concierge medicine, prescription review and approval, lab interpretation, mental health management, and more.
Physicians work independently and are responsible for diagnostic and therapeutic decision-making within industry and locally established standards of care, clinical practice guidelines, and organization policies and procedures. The content of medical decision-making focuses on common conditions that would present within an episodic, acute, or primary care medical practice.

Job Title: Full-Time Remote Telehealth Primary Care/Urgent Care Physician
Job Description:
We are looking for culturally responsive, well-respected, and entrepreneurial physicians (MDs and DOs) to provide virtual urgent care and primary care for one of our partners and serve as clinician leaders on a full-time employment basis. Physicians must be comfortable treating patients of all ages, including infants, children, adults, and older adults. For this position, physicians must have recent experience with all age populations, including experience providing care for an infant in the last 12 months. Physicians must also be comfortable treating across the entire primary care spectrum, including contraceptives, HIV prevention, and mental health medication management.
Physicians work independently and are responsible for diagnostic and therapeutic decision-making within industry and locally established standards of care, clinical practice guidelines, and organization policies and procedures. The content of medical decision-making focuses on common conditions that would present within an episodic, acute, or primary care medical practice. Additionally, there are several opportunities to participate as a clinician leader by means of developing and improving clinical protocols and processes, and working with a large network of clinicians to ensure high-quality patient care.

What Matters To You
Are you looking for a career option that supports work-life balance and an ability to build a flexible schedule, all while maintaining financial well-being? We want you to be a part of building Sound’s Telemedicine service line as we launch the first nationally-scaled, fully-resourced, hospital medicine-focused telemedicine program. Success Happens When you Start With your People
Telemedicine is a proven approach and is now considered a standard of care option in multiple specialties, including psychology, neurology, critical care, and hospital medicine. We strive to be the practice of choice for providers and the partner of choice for hospitals across the country. This innovative model of care delivery will help providers find balance and joy in their careers as they add a new dimension to their scope of practice.

Our Company
Cerebral is a one-stop shop for high-quality mental health care.

Our team will not stop building, growing, and iterating until everyone, everywhere can access high-quality mental health care without the high cost, wait times, and stigma.
We recently became the fastest mental health company ever to unicorn status, having raised over $162 million and achieved a valuation above $1.2 billion raised. Cerebral's investors include Silver Lake, Access Industries, Bill Ackman, Chris Burch, WestCap, and Oak HC/FT.
It is just the beginning for Cerebral, and we need your help as we transform access to high-quality mental health care in the United States and beyond.

What is DocMJ?

What Matters To You
Are you looking for a career option that supports work-life balance and an ability to build a flexible schedule, all while maintaining financial well-being? We want you to be a part of building Sound’s Telemedicine service line as we launch the first nationally-scaled, fully-resourced, hospital medicine-focused telemedicine program. Success Happens When you Start With your People
Telemedicine is a proven approach and is now considered a standard of care option in multiple specialties, including psychology, neurology, critical care, and hospital medicine. The telemedicine care model is aligned with Sound’s vision of being the unmatched leader in improving quality and reducing the cost of healthcare for patients in the communities we serve, particularly those serving rural populations with limited access to care. We strive to be the practice of choice for providers and the partner of choice for hospitals across the country. This innovative model of care delivery will help providers find balance and joy in their careers as they add a new dimension to their scope of practice.

TeamHealth is seeking a full-time emergency physician to deliver safe, high-quality care with our group at Baptist Medical Center East in Montgomery, Alabama. This facility is part of the Baptist Health System, which is also comprised of Baptist Medical Center South and Prattville Baptist Hospital.

Job Title: Full-Time Remote Telehealth Primary Care/Urgent Care Physician
Job Description:
We are looking for culturally responsive, well-respected, and entrepreneurial physicians (MDs and DOs) to provide virtual urgent care and primary care for one of our partners and serve as clinician leaders on a full-time employment basis. Physicians must be comfortable treating patients of all ages, including infants, children, adults, and older adults. For this position, physicians must have recent experience with all age populations, including experience providing care for an infant in the last 12 months. What is DocMJ?

What Matters To You

Success Happens When you Start With your People

This innovative model of care delivery will help providers find balance and joy in their careers as they add a new dimension to their scope of practice.
